  "prompt": "Does four wheel drive consume more fuel than two wheel drive?",
  "response": "Generally, yes. Vehicles with four-wheel drive (4WD) systems tend to consume more fuel than their two-wheel drive (2WD) counterparts. This is because 4WD systems are typically heavier and more complex, which can lead to increased mechanical resistance and higher weight. The additional components such as transfer cases, differentials, and drive shafts require more power to operate, which translates to higher fuel consumption. Additionally, when 4WD is engaged, power is distributed to all four wheels, increasing the overall load on the engine.\n\nHowever, it is important to note that fuel consumption can also be influenced by other factors such as driving habits, terrain, and vehicle design. Therefore, while 4WD systems may generally consume more fuel, the difference in fuel efficiency between 4WD and 2WD can vary depending on specific circumstances.",
